<!-- Font configuration for the Default Font Tweaks option
Provides metric and menu-specific font data for Vanilla UI Plus; created with the "Font Metrics container_menu" testbed mod (moddb.com/mods/vanilla-ui-plus/addons/font-metrics)
WRITTEN BY AXONIS FOR VANILLA UI PLUS; MODIFIED SEPTEMBER 2022

Sorted from smaller to bigger
#2 - Condensed font, standard menu & list font, designed to occupy as little space as possible and still be perfectly readable
#3 - Looks small, and in VUI+ it actually is
#7 - Outlined font, use for subtitles and the HUD
#1 - Default font, used in tutorials mostly; the engine switches to this font when no <font> tags are being used in text
#5 - Terminal font, don't use for anything else
#6 - Larger font, use for headings
#4 - Pip-Boy Heading font, used for the top-left headings on Pip-Boy menus only
#8 - Huge font, use for uppercase titles only -->

<!-- Vertical alignment of a font's midline -->
<_VUI+FontY_1> 8 </_VUI+FontY_1>
